                <head>No. 79.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received July 22.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Uprising of Indians and Jamaica negroes at Bluefields extremely unfortunate. They
                    restored Chief Clarence and set up government. Presence of United States marines
                    prevents further bloodshed. Minister Madriz goes down and will take letters from
                    me advising Americans of their duty to the sovereign Government.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
